FBIS4-59926 "drnes097_l_94006" FBIS-NES-94-097 Daily Report 19 May 1994 ISRAEL IDF Lifts Hebron Curfew; TIPH Resumes Activities IDF Lifts Hebron Curfew; TIPH Resumes Activities TA1905085194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0700 GMT 19 May 94 TA1905085194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Hebrew BFN [Text] Last night the IDF [Israel Defense Forces] lifted the curfew that had been imposed in Hebron in the wake of the incidents last Monday [16 May]. The TIPH [Temporary International Presence in Hebron] spokesman told our correspondent Moti Amir that during the curfew, the observers were not allowed to leave their headquarters and were actually held under house arrest. According to him, TIPH personnel resumed their duties this morning.
